term_inventory_greek.meaning:
selfish ambition, faction, strife
the service of a party, party spirit;
feud, faction, 2Cor. 12:20; contentious disposition, selfish ambition, Gal. 5:20; Phil. 1:17; 2:3;
Jas. 3:14; by implication untowardness, disobedience, Rom. 2:8; Jas. 3:16*

to have an ambition, aspire to a goal
primarily to be ambitious of honor;
by implication to exert one's self to accomplish a thing, use one's utmost efforts, endeavor earnestly, aspire to a goal Rom. 15:20; 2Cor. 5:9; 1Thess. 4:11*
